s Gaston Oscar Glass''' in [[Paris]] and died in [[Santa Monica, California]]. He was the father of the composer [[Paul Glass]] (born in 1934).\n\n==Partial filmography==\n{{Div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* ''[[The Corsican Brothers (1917 film)|The Corsican Brothers]]'' (1917)\n* ''[[Let's Elope (film)|Let's Elope]]'' (1919)\n* ''[[Oh, You Women!]]'' (1919)\n* ''[[God's Crucible]]'' (2020)\n* ''[[Humoresque (1920 film)|Humoresque]]'' (1920)\n* ''[[The World and His Wife]]'' (1920)\n* ''[[The Branded Woman]]'' (1920)\n* ''[[Her Winning Way]]'' (1921)\n* ''[[There Are No Villains]]'' (1921)\n* ''[[Glass Houses (1922 film)|Glass Houses]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[Little Miss Smiles]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[The Song of Life (1922 film)|The Song of Life]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[I Am the Law (1922 film)|I Am the Law]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[The Kingdom Within]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[The Hero (1923 film)|The Hero]]'' (1923)\n* ''[[Gimme (film)|Gimme]]'' (1923) as Clinton Ferris\n* ''[[Trouping with Ellen]]'' (1924)\n* ''[[I Am the Man (film)|I Am the Man]]'' (1924)\n* ''[[After the Ball (1924 film)|After the Ball]]'' (1924)\n* ''[[The Mad Marriage (1925 film)|The Mad Marriage]]'' (1925)\n* ''[[The Bad Lands]]'' (1925)\n* ''[[The Scarlet West]]'' (1925)\n* ''[[Parisian Nights]]'' (1925)\n* ''[[The Flying Fool (1925 film)|The Flying Fool]]'' (1926)\n* ''[[Subway Sadie]]'' (1926)\n* ''[[Things Wives Tell]]'' (1926)\n* ''[[The Call of the Klondike]]'' (1926)\n* ''[[Sweet Daddies]]'' (1926)\n* ''[[The Jazz Girl]]'' (1926)\n* ''[[Exclusive Rights (film)|Exclusive Rights]]'' (1926)\n* ''[[Tentacles of the North]]'' (1926)\n* ''[[Wives at Auction]]'' (1926)\n* ''[[Sinews of Steel]]'' (1927)\n* ''[[The Show Girl]]'' (1927)\n* ''[[The Gorilla (1927 film)|The Gorilla]]'' (1927)\n* ''[[The Wife's Relations]]'' (1928)\n* ''[[The Red Mark]]'' (1928)\n* ''[[Name the Woman (1928 film)|Name the Woman]]'' (1928)\n* ''[[A Gentleman Preferred]]'' (1928)\n* ''[[Broken Barriers (1928 film)|Broken Barriers]]'' (1928)\n* ''[[Geraldine (19